This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the syntactic analysis of online writing and language variation in social media. It could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it explores the link between language and social networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) as it deals with the analysis of language variation. It could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the use of a mixture-of-experts model. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it explores the impact of social networks on language use.
